replies.bodyText:
Now I remember that at some point I got into a state where the OpenRDT app was immediately returning its result rather than first going through its UI flow and then returning. That led me to this Stackoverflow post. The OpenRDT examples I was sent (not public, unfortunately) do use setFlags(0).

getLaunchIntentForPackage("com.your.package.here") would create an intent with Intent.FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK added by default, so call: in.setFlags(0);

Always creating the target activity and avoiding the FLAG_ACTIVITY_NEW_TASK flag seems like the way to go to me. There are differences in Android versions with how the other launch modes work and their behavior will also depend on whether or not an activity is already in memory.

